description:
Software development and consulting company offering high end solutions for various business needs. Our expertise in cutting edge technologies and strictly adopting Agile-development principles have made us one of the premier technology consulting company worldwide.

We started off as a small team in 2006 to build amazing products and solutions for companies that need them. Over time, we‚Äôve built over 500 applications for our clients across the globe. Many of them got funded and one of them got acquired by google.

Today, we‚Äôre a team of 500+ people. We‚Äôve opened up an office in the US, Australia, and Canada our most significant markets, to get much closer to our customers. 

Our strength lies in building and supporting world-class Web and Mobile Applications. The technology stack includes but is not limited to Ruby on Rails, Phoenix Elixir, Android, iOS(swift), Go Lang, Nodejs, ReactJs, and Angular. To leverage the strength of the technologies, we use Micro-Services-based architecture for most of our applications.

With more than 35+ years of domain expertise of our practitioners in this space we have launched our Enterprise division to cater to the needs of large organizations with SAP-ERP, OpenText, UiPath, Oracle & Asset Management System ‚Äì Maximo. And our clientele in this space includes various Fortune 500 companies.

Our enterprise-focused services are around Asset Management (Maximo), Content management (Documentum, MS Sharepoint), Cloud (AWS, Azure), ERP, RPA, CAD, HCM & SAP.

Services we offer on Enterprise- Consulting, Maximo Implementation, Maximo Upgrades, Reporting, Integration, Date Uploading & Support.

From a bookshelf in 2017 to a real-life meeting in 2025.

Our very own team member Premkumar S recently met Frans Johansson, the author of The Medici Effect, a book that inspired a decade of innovative thinking. A full-circle moment, and a reminder that ideas truly grow at the intersections.


#Innovation #TheMediciEffect #TeamSedin #FullCircleMoment #InspiredAtWork
company_updates.reshared_post_author_headline:
VP - Operations & Corporate Development | GCC at Sedin
[Expert-Generalist | Business Operations | Startup Enabler | Mentor | Problem Solver | Design Thinker]
company_updates.reshared_post_description:
A surreal moment.
Back in 2017, my mentor handed me a book and said, ‚ÄúYou need to read this".It was¬†-The Medici Effect. I didn‚Äôt know much about it ‚Äî just that it talked about intersections, innovation, and how great ideas often come from the most unexpected combinations. I read it cover to cover. 
Something about it just stuck with me. 

Recently, I picked it up again ‚Äî this time to go deeper and apply the concepts more intentionally. It felt timely. It felt necessary.

And today‚Ä¶
I got to meet Frans Johansson ‚Äî the person who wrote that book and sparked that shift in me all those years ago. A full-circle moment I never saw coming.
We had such a meaningful conversation. I‚Äôm so grateful he made time despite a packed schedule. 

I walked away happy and energized- With a big smile.
And yes, he signed my book:¬†‚ÄúSee you at the intersection.‚Äù
Still smiling üòÅ 

By the way ‚Äî the book came out 21 years ago. And yet, it still feels like it was written for today. That‚Äôs what happens when something is rooted in first principles ‚Äî it just keeps staying relevant.

#TheMediciEffect #Innovation #Creativity #IntersectionalThinking #FransJohansson #Leadership #Gratitude #BooksThatChangeYou
